        "The classification report shows that the CNN achieves an overall accuracy of about 78%, with macro and weighted averages around 0.78. The model performs consistently across classes without strong bias toward any single class. Performance varies across categories. The model performs best on forest images, with precision of 0.92 and recall of 0.94. Buildings, mountain, and street show moderate performance, with F1-scores in the mid to high 0.7 range. Glacier and sea have weaker recall, 0.65 and 0.71, respectively. Many glacier and sea examples are misclassified, likely confused with visually similar classes such as mountains or sky/water regions. The confusion matrix shows misclassifications primarily between visually similar categories."
      ],
