      "source": [
        "Part 2"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kC_ra3YGh9v6"
      },
      "source": [
        "For transfer learning, I picked ResNet50. ResNet50 is a deep convolutional neural network with 50 layers and is known for its use of residual connections, which help mitigate the vanishing gradient problem and enable the training of very deep networks. A pre-trained version of ResNet50 (trained on the ImageNet dataset) was used as a feature extractor, with its top classification layers removed. The base model was frozen to keep the learned features, and new dense layers were added to adapt it to the current classification task.\n",
        "\n",
        "Transfer learning with ResNet50 improves performance because the model has already learned generalizable features from a large and diverse dataset (ImageNet). These learned representations can be reused for the current task, allowing the model to achieve higher accuracy and converge faster compared to training a CNN from scratch."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 16,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "uImLVHgGiEll",
        "outputId": "5ae639f4-2dd7-4cb4-ee95-4f168329acc7"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Downloading data from https://storage.googleapis.com/tensorflow/keras-applications/resnet/resnet50_weights_tf_dim_ordering_tf_kernels_notop.h5\n",
            "\u001b[1m94765736/94765736\u001b[0m \u001b[32m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[37m\u001b[0m \u001b[1m7s\u001b[0m 0us/step\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# load pretrained ResNet50 model - trained on ImageNet\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.applications import ResNet50\n",
        "\n",
        "base_model = ResNet50(\n",
        "  weights='imagenet', # pretrained weights\n",
        "  include_top=False, # remove original classifier\n",
        "  input_shape=(150,150,3)\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# freeze base model - retain learned features\n",
        "base_model.trainable = False\n",
        "\n",
        "# build transfer learning model\n",
        "model_tl = models.Sequential([\n",
        "  base_model,\n",
        "  layers.GlobalAveragePooling2D(), # reduce feature maps\n",
        "  layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n",
        "  layers.Dense(num_classes, activation='softmax')\n",
        "])"
      ]
    },
